Privacy Policy
 
This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose your personal information, and outlines your related rights when using our services. Protecting your personal information is our top priority.
 
1. Information We Collect
1.1 Information You Provide to Us: Information you provide to us during your use of our application, such as your name, email address, and payment information.
 
1.2 Automatically Collected Information: Information we may automatically collect when you use our application, including but not limited to your device information, operating system version, application version, and unique device identifiers.
 
2. Use of Information
2.1 Providing Services: We may use collected information to provide you with our services, including but not limited to processing payments, sending you notifications, and providing customer support.
 
2.2 Improving Services: We may use collected information to improve our services and develop new features.
 
3. Information Disclosure
3.1 Service Providers: We may engage third-party companies and individuals to assist us in providing services and may need to share certain information with them. These third parties are authorized to use your personal information only as necessary to provide services to us.
 
3.2 Legal Requirements: We may disclose your personal information in response to lawful requests by public authorities, including to meet national security or law enforcement requirements.
 
4. Data Security
We take reasonable security measures to protect your personal information from loss, misuse, or alteration. While we strive to protect your personal information, please be aware that no method of transmission or storage over the internet is completely secure.
 
5. Rights
5.1 Access and Correction: You have the right to access and correct personal information we hold about you.
 
5.2 Data Deletion: In certain circumstances, you have the right to request deletion of your personal information.
 
6. In-App Purchases
Our application may contain in-app purchase features, allowing you to purchase additional functionalities or services within the application. These in-app purchase transactions will be handled by Apple Inc., and we do not collect or store payment information related to these transactions.
 
7. User Conduct Guidelines
7.1 Users must not post any content that is objectionable, abusive, harassing, threatening, defamatory, libelous, obscene, or illegal.
 
7.2 Users must not use this application for any illegal activities, including but not limited to violating others' privacy, infringing copyrights, distributing malware, or other harmful content.
 
8. Content Moderation
8.1 We reserve the right to review, edit, or delete any content that violates this agreement.
 
8.2 All content posted by users will be automatically filtered to detect and block objectionable content.
 
9. Reporting Mechanism
9.1 Users can report any content they find objectionable or abusive through the "Report" button within the app.
 
9.2 We will review all reported content within a reasonable time and take appropriate actions, including but not limited to removing the content or disabling the user's account.
 
10. User Blocking
10.1 Users can block any other users they find objectionable or abusive to prevent further harassment.
 
10.2 Blocked users will not be able to view or interact with the users who have blocked them.
 
11. Changes to Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of any updates to the Privacy Policy through in-app notifications or by posting the updated Privacy Policy on our website.